From: CAT/EPT Navier-Stokes Bridge Program
Date: 2026-03-08
Subject: [PATCH] Add CAT/EPT entropic-time bridge for PyAnsys (PyMAPDL + PyFluent + PyAEDT)

Applies to: multiphysics/integration/ (not upstream pymapdl/pyfluent/pyaedt)

This patch is NOT applied to the upstream PyAnsys packages. The upstream
repos (pymapdl, pyfluent, pyaedt) are used as-is via their published Python
APIs. All CAT/EPT integration code lives within the entropic-time repo.

The upstream packages are tracked in external_clone mode in:
  tools/multiphysics/vendor_workflow_manifest.json

Vendor metadata:
  multiphysics/external/pymapdl_vendor_metadata.yaml
  multiphysics/external/pyfluent_vendor_metadata.yaml
  multiphysics/external/pyaedt_vendor_metadata.yaml

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Summary of CAT/EPT additions (new files in this repo):
--------------------------------------------------------------------

  multiphysics/integration/pyansys_entropic_bridge.py
    Three-backend entropic bridge for ANSYS physics:
      run_pyansys_mapdl_thermal()   — thermal-structural (PyMAPDL)
      run_pyansys_fluent_cfd()      — CFD thermal-hydraulics (PyFluent)
      run_pyansys_maxwell_em()      — Maxwell EM field solve (PyAEDT)

    Each function:
      - Accepts CAT/EPT contract inputs: tau_ent_0, lambda_rate, dt
      - Returns CAT/EPT contract outputs: tau_ent_next, delta_s_i, lambda_eff,
        residual_norm, constraint_norm, converged
      - Supports backend_mode in {stub, analytical, native, native_strict}
      - Returns interop dict for: geant4, opentopas, qutip, mapdl/fluent/maxwell, pynucastro

  tools/multiphysics/validate_pyansys_mapdl_native_strict.py
    Preflight validator for MAPDL bridge (7 check groups, exit 0/1/2).

  multiphysics/integration/registry.py  (modified)
    Added 3 registry entries:
      pyansys_mapdl_thermal_entropic
      pyansys_fluent_cfd_entropic
      pyansys_maxwell_em_entropic

  multiphysics/qf_qutip_dsl/ir.py  (modified)
    Added 3 IR dataclass nodes:
      PyAnsysMAPDLThermalNode
      PyAnsysFluentCFDNode
      PyAnsysMaxwellEMNode

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Physics coupling chain:
--------------------------------------------------------------------

  Geant4/OpenTOPAS  →  dose_gy
       ↓
  PyMAPDL thermal   →  temperature_max_k, thermal_stress_mpa
       ↓
  PyFluent CFD      →  outlet_temperature_k, heat_removal_w, pressure_drop_pa
       ↓
  PyAEDT Maxwell    →  b_field_max_t, force_n, inductance_h
       ↓
  Geant4            ←  G4UniformMagField (beam optics)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Entropic coupling formulas:
--------------------------------------------------------------------

  MAPDL:   lambda_eff = lambda_rate * (1 + alpha_T  * delta_T)
  Fluent:  lambda_eff = lambda_rate * (1 + beta_flow * delta_T_coolant)
  Maxwell: lambda_eff = lambda_rate * (1 + gamma_B  * B_max_T)

  where delta_T = T_max_k - T_ambient,  delta_T_coolant = T_outlet - T_inlet

--------------------------------------------------------------------
Environment variables for native backend configuration:
--------------------------------------------------------------------

  CATEPT_PYANSYS_MAPDL_HOST        (default: 127.0.0.1)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_MAPDL_PORT        (default: 50052)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_FLUENT_HOST       (default: 127.0.0.1)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_FLUENT_PORT       (default: 50051)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_AEDT_VERSION      (e.g. "2024.2"; default: latest)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_NATIVE_TIMEOUT    (gRPC timeout in seconds)
  CATEPT_PYANSYS_NATIVE_MOCK       (set "1" to force fallback; for CI/testing)

--------------------------------------------------------------------
No modifications to upstream source required.
--------------------------------------------------------------------
